1. Java Persistence API (JPA)
Definition
JPA stands for Java Persistence API.
It is a Java specification (JSR 338) for storing and retrieving data from a database.
It defines interfaces and annotations but does not provide an implementation.
Features
Standard API for ORM
Uses annotations like:
@Entity
@Table
@Id
@Column
Portable across different ORM frameworks.
2. Hibernate
Definition

Hibernate is an ORM (Object Relational Mapping) framework that implements JPA.

It converts Java objects into database tables.

Features
Implements JPA
Generates SQL automatically
Maps Java objects to database tables
Handles CRUD operations
Supports caching and lazy loading
3. Spring Data JPA
Definition

Spring Data JPA is built on top of JPA.

It does not implement JPA but simplifies database programming by reducing boilerplate code.

Features
Uses Hibernate internally
Automatically manages transactions
Automatically creates SQL queries
Provides built-in repository methods

Example:

findAll()

save()

delete()

findById()
